LAFIA – The Nasarawa State House of Assembly, on Monday reelected Alhaji Ibrahim Balarabe-Abdullahi to serve as the Speaker in the 6th Assembly. The reelection of the speaker was unopposed after he was nominated by Mohammed Okpoku, member representing Udege Logo (APC) and it was seconded by Alhaji Aliyu Dogara during the inauguration of the 6th Assembly in Lafia. The speaker was sworn in by the Clerk of the House, Ego Maikeffi Abashe. Nehemiah Tsetse Dandaura, a member representing Akwanga North constituency, was elected Deputy Speaker. Okpoku explained that the nomination of Balarabe Abdullahi was based on his leadership qualities and track records of achievements. In his acceptance speech, the speaker appreciated his colleagues for the rare privilege to serve them again as the speaker of the sixth Assembly He, however, promised smooth working relationship with the members in the 6thh Assembly.